{"questionId":"7446","questionHtml":"<p>A container is filled with a mixture of helium and oxygen at the same temperature. The molar mass&nbsp;of helium is 4 g mol<sup>–1</sup> and that of oxygen is 32 g mol<sup>–1</sup>.</p>\n<p>What is the ratio <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{average speed of helium molecules}}}}{{{\\text{average speed of oxygen molecules}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>average speed of helium molecules</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>average speed of oxygen molecules</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{8}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>8</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{\\sqrt 8 }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\sqrt 8 }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msqrt>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n    </msqrt>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;8</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7446","referenceCode":"18N.1.SL.TZ0.11","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A container is filled with a mixture of helium and oxygen at the same temperature. The molar mass of helium is 4 g mol–1 and that of oxygen is 32 g mol–1. What is the ratio average","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"11","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2